args: Did you hear the news? Apparently some\nresearchers at the academy died bizarre\ndeaths.
Makes you wonder what sort of research\nthey were up to, don't it?
To think the rumors would spread so far\nin mere days...
Listen well, Akasha. No one must learn\nof our research on that tome.
We will cease it at once, and I will see the\ngrimoire itself sealed away.
We've heard the news, Akasha.\nDeaths, at that academy of yours?
I've always known that place was useless.\nWhat good is a school if it can't even keep\nits own students alive?!
Complications can happen during research,\nmother, and sometimes—

You KNOW I was against it from the start!
Sending her to that institution just to
curry favor with the headmaster... Such
NONSENSE!
It seemed wise at the time, but...
The headmaster can have no qualms with\nus withdrawing her now.
You are to stop attending that academy,\nAkasha. Do you understand?
I have already dispatched a letter\nformalizing your withdrawal.\nYou shall research no longer.
You will be attending teatime from\ntomorrow, and parties as well.
You'll need new dresses as well, and room\nto store them. You can start by throwing\nout all those musty old books.
After all, what need will you have for\nbooks and research? Your days will be\nspent in blissful luxury from here on!
(It's fine. Nothing matters.\nIt's fine. Nothing matters...)
(Nothing. Not my research, not my\ngrimoire...not me.)
(There's nothing I can do. Nothing I can do.\nNothing...)
(...But. But but but but but. I want more.\nMore. More more more more MORE.)
(Nothing matters. But more. Nothing.\nIt's fine. But more...)
A lonely, lonely maze of solitude...
Who indeed, my dear. And who could say?
But that matters not. Let's have some fun!\nHow about a riddle? You like riddles, yes?
Searching for the truth is the place where\nyou feel most at home, after all.
Wh-what could you possibly know\nabout me?
Everything, my dear. That which was,\nthat which is, and that which will be.\nAll of it.
But... No. That can't be possible.
And yet you know I speak the truth.\nHere I stand before you, the image\nof what you can attain.
A gate lies before you. One shut tight\nwith a lock of silver.
What could be through that gate, I wonder?
And like all gates, you face two options\nwith this one.
Turn your back and walk away, or open\nit and walk straight through.
Spend all the time you like imagining what\nlies within, but only by opening it will\nyou know the truth.
I can't just leave without opening it.
Acquiring knowledge is the only pleasure\nI've ever known.
Regardless of what people said or did,\nI was okay being alone because I could\nescape into the pursuit of knowledge.
But that option has been taken from you.
...Yes. With my thesis, and my grimoire,\ntoo.
And now, even the place you found for\nyourself, the knowledge you have clung\nto for oh so long, has been taken away.
This riddle's answer is whatever you wish.
You always surrender, so sure that nothing\nyou do will matter. But is that true?
What does the true Akasha want?\nWhat has she always wanted?
More, more, more, more, more, more,\nmore, more, more, more, more, more...
MORE! I WANT TO KNOW MORE!
A-Akasha! What in the blazes is going on?!\nWhat is this?!
Come unto me, O great knowledge.
All shall be nothingness.\nMy doubts have fled.
